rComments: She's a really nice prof, teaches in both French and English. She uses the textbooks a lot, but they are more like work books. Gives lots of good examples and helps to understand. Grades come from biweekly quizzes, 2 written papers, oral exam, 5 grammar quizzes, 5 listening quizzes and the final exam. No midterms. Overall really enjoyed the class.

Estela is not only a very caring prof, but she also gives great feedback on papers. She always makes time to help students outside of class hours, whether it is to review exams or discuss the course content. She can be quite specific in her correction of writing productions, but it only contributes to the learning experience.

super friendly and great professor but she's pretty strict when she marks, you either 100% get it or if you make a mistake then it's wrong (which makes sense cause its a language class and for the advanced level but still) she wants her class to succeed so always ask questions and she'll clarify anything !

Mostly read from the slides, sometimes not able to meet with you, bad grading criteria, hard marker, not really explain things in detail. I personally got I good mark because my first langague is spanish, but she is hard with students that don't know the language well and is not fair overall. She gives a grammar quiz ever week!
